"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-lifestyle-celeb-news-local-celebs-rachel-siya-kolisi-springboks-wags-tatjana-smith-shoenmaker-joel-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbLifestyle\\u00bbCeleb News\\u00bbLocal Celebs\\u00bb'So proud': Rachel Kolisi, Springboks WAGS show Tatjana love  Rachel Kolisi showed sister-in-law Tatjana Smith some love after she bagged South Africa their first gold medal at the Paris Olympics 2024.  Siya Kolisi's wife, Rachel Kolisi showed her sister-in-lawTatjana Smithsome love after the South African swimmer won the women's 100m breaststroke at the Paris Olympics 2024 on Monday 29 July.  South African swimmer Tatjana Smith bagged South Africa their first gold medal when she won the women's 100m breaststroke at the Paris Olympics 2024 on Monday 29 July. She finished ahead of China's\\u00a0Qianting Tang\\u00a0and Ireland's\\u00a0Mona McSharry.  The Olympic swimmer took to Instagram to celebrate, and dedicate her win to South Africa. Take a look\\u2026  \\\"For my community, for South Africa. Now for the 200 \\u23f0,\\\" she captioned the post.  A post shared by -TATJANA-SCHOENMAKER- (@tatjanaschoen)  Tatjana is married to Joel Smith, who is Rachel Kolisi's brother. Rachel took to the comments section, along with other Springboks WAGS to show Tatjana some love.  \\\"So so proud of you Tati! Well done \\u2764\\ufe0f,\\\" commented Rachel.  \\\"Woohoooo!!! WELL DONE\\u00a0@tatjanaschoen\\u00a0\\ud83e\\udd73\\ud83d\\ude4c\\ud83e\\udd73\\ud83d\\ude01\\ud83d\\udc95,\\\" commented Anlia Etzebeth, the wife of Springbok Eben Etzebeth.  \\\"\\u2764\\ufe0f\\ud83e\\udd47\\ud83c\\uddff\\ud83c\\udde6,\\\" commented Springbok Damian Gaza.  Here'ssix things to know about Tatjana.  Tatjana revealed that it took a village to get her where she is today and she knows they would be so proud of her. She expressed that she dedicates the win to her village, and her country, South Africa.  \\\"The emotions were really \\u2026 it took a village to get me where I am today. I know they would have been proud, even if I did not get a medal, but it was really for them,\\\" she said.  \\\"It was for everyone that has been with me, who believed in me and for my country as well. Our hashtag is 'for my country \\u2026' it really is, just to inspire someone at home and to know that they do not have to disqualify themselves and potentially be an Olympic champion,\\\" she continued.  Find out more aboutTatjana's husband here.  Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or by emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.comor sending a WhatsApp to 060 011 021 1. You can also follow@TheSAnews on XandThe South African on Facebookfor the latest news.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in t